```

CRITICAL: The `colors/` directory is inside `base/` which auto-imports all `.nix` files. The files in `colors/` are NOT modules — they're plain attrsets with no `{ ... }:` function wrapper. Clan-core's auto-import should skip subdirectories (it typically only imports direct children). Verify this won't conflict — if needed, make the files return attrsets WITHOUT being modules.

Actually, clan-core's roster module uses `homeProfilesPath` and loads profile directories. The profile name is "base" which maps to the `base/` directory. It auto-imports all `.nix` files DIRECTLY in the directory. Subdirectories like `colors/` are NOT auto-imported. So plain Nix data files in `colors/` will work fine — they're explicitly imported by `colors.nix`.

