Update the Cloudflare Tunnel module to consume exports from other services, so ingress backend URLs can be auto-resolved instead of hardcoded.

File: /home/brittonr/git/onix-core/modules/cloudflare-tunnel/default.nix

The `perInstance` currently is:
```nix
perInstance = { instanceName, extendSettings, ... }:
```

Change to accept exports:
```nix
perInstance = { instanceName, extendSettings, exports, ... }:
```

Then inside the `nixosModule`, after the `localSettings` binding, add logic to resolve ingress URLs from exports. The idea: if an ingress value is a placeholder like `"auto:vaultwarden"`, resolve it from exports. Otherwise keep the manual URL.

Actually, a simpler and more backward-compatible approach: add a NEW option `autoIngress` that maps hostnames to service export names, separate from the manual `ingress`. Then merge both at evaluation time.

Wait - let me think about this more carefully. The current `ingress` option maps hostnames to backend URLs:
```nix
ingress = {
  "vault.robitzs.ch" = "http://localhost:8222";
  "auth.robitzs.ch" = "http://localhost:9081";
  "clonadic.blr.dev" = "http://localhost:8080";
};
```

The cleanest approach is to keep `ingress` as-is for manual overrides, but add a helper that builds ingress entries from exports. Add a new option:

In the `interface.options` section, add:
```nix
autoIngress = mkOption {
  type = attrsOf str;
  default = { };
  description = ''
    Automatically resolve ingress backend URLs from service exports.
    Maps hostnames to export service endpoint names.
    Example: { "vault.robitzs.ch" = "vaultwarden"; }
    The service must export serviceEndpoints.<name> with a url field.
    Manual ingress entries take precedence over auto-resolved ones.
  '';
};
```

Then in the nixosModule `let` block, resolve autoIngress from exports and merge with manual ingress:

```nix
# Resolve auto-ingress from service exports
autoIngress = localSettings.autoIngress or { };
resolvedAutoIngress = lib.mapAttrs (_hostname: serviceName:
  let
    matchingInstances = lib.filterAttrs (_: v: 
      (v.serviceEndpoints.${serviceName} or null) != null
    ) (exports.instances or { });
    firstMatch = lib.head (lib.attrValues matchingInstances);
  in
  if matchingInstances != { } 
  then firstMatch.serviceEndpoints.${serviceName}.url
  else throw "cloudflare-tunnel: No export found for service '${serviceName}' (referenced by autoIngress)"
